# Public routes — PII contracts

ADR + `AGENTS.md §5`. Every public surface returns through a typed DTO with an explicit field allowlist, asserted by a Playwright test.

## `/verify-card/[number]` — frozen contract

Allowed response fields, exactly:

```ts
type PublicCardDTO = {
  number: string;
  memberName: string | null;
  memberType: "VIP" | "BUSINESS" | null;
  status: "ACTIVE" | "INACTIVE" | "EXPIRED" | "NOT_FOUND";
  expiresAt: string | null; // ISO date
};
```

Anything else is a leak. No `userId`, no `email`, no `phone`, no `stripeCustomerId`, no `createdAt`, no `country`, no `city`.

## Constant-shape response

`NOT_FOUND` returns the same 5 keys, only `status = "NOT_FOUND"`:

```ts
const NOT_FOUND: PublicCardDTO = {
  number: "",
  memberName: null,
  memberType: null,
  status: "NOT_FOUND",
  expiresAt: null,
};
```

**Why**: response-shape and length differences are an existence oracle. An attacker can enumerate which card numbers exist by comparing response sizes. Constant shape kills the oracle.

## Cache policy

```ts
export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";
export const fetchCache = "force-no-store";
export const revalidate = 0;
```

NO ISR, NO `revalidate: 120`, NO `tags`. Cards can be revoked instantly; a 2-minute stale window is a security incident.

## Rate limit + Turnstile

Per IP: 10/min. Per card number: 5/10min. Turnstile token required on the lookup form. See `09-security-headers.mdc`.

## Playwright assertion

Every public surface that touches DB has this test shape:

```ts
test("verify-card response contains exactly the allowed PII keys", async ({ request }) => {
  const res = await request.get("/api/cards/lookup/VIP-UA-XXXXX");
  const body = await res.json();
  expect(Object.keys(body).sort()).toEqual(
    ["expiresAt", "memberName", "memberType", "number", "status"].sort(),
  );
});

test("verify-card NOT_FOUND has same key shape as hit", async ({ request }) => {
  const hit = await (await request.get("/api/cards/lookup/VIP-UA-XXXXX")).json();
  const miss = await (await request.get("/api/cards/lookup/NOT-REAL-12345")).json();
  expect(Object.keys(hit).sort()).toEqual(Object.keys(miss).sort());
});
```

If you add a field, you update the test. If you forget, the test fails.

## Adding a new public route

Use the `/pii-audit` command to verify the new route has:

1. A typed DTO (not a raw row spread).
2. A constant-shape response.
3. `cache: 'no-store'` if it touches per-user data.
4. Rate limit + (where applicable) Turnstile.
5. A Playwright assertion on the response key set.

All five. No exceptions.

